eal / exitall                 Terminates every connection and saves files
 
   Format:
      ;eal                    Terminates every connection
      ;eal <minutes>          Terminates every connection after a delay 
 
   Notes:
      Use this command to terminate every connection immediately, without 
         waiting for every world to respond.
      This command automatically save data files. To exit without saving files
         use the ';panic' command.
      Use the ';exit' or ';xxit' commands to close an individual connection.
      See also the help for ';abortselfdestruct'.
 
   User commands:
      eal / exitall
